      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument isn't that religious freedom is unimportant, but that it must operate within the boundaries of the law that protects everyone. A mature democracy seeks to harmonize these rights, meaning religious freedom is protected *as long as* it doesn't infringe upon the fundamental rights of others. When a belief directly causes harm or denies rights to others, the law must prioritize the protection of those vulnerable citizens.",
      "source": "target",
